# Git Push After Changes

When you modify files in this repository, commit and push to `origin/main` before finishing the task.

Remote: `https://github.com/shahmeerabdul/medallion-dwh-blueprint.git`

## Workflow

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to review changes.
2. Stage only relevant files (never `.env` or secrets).
3. Write a concise commit message focused on why.
4. Commit, then `git push origin main`.
5. Confirm with `git status` that the branch is up to date.

Only skip push if the user explicitly says not to push, or if push fails due to auth/network (report the failure).
